Has this ever happened to you?? More often these days I will think of a story, be so excited and passionate about what I'm going to say and something distracts me. I mean something small distracts me and BOOM! The whole story is gone and I just stare at the person with nothing to say. 🤣🤣🤣. I have never been officially diagnosed with ADHD, but I'm pretty sure I have it. I was so consumed on getting a definitive answer on if I had it or not. I wanted a medical professional to tell me YES you have it or NO you don't. Then someone asked me "what will that diagnosis do for you? What do you want to accomplish once you find out? Will it change you for the good or will it make you feel like something is wrong with you, like you're not in the norm?" I sat with those questions for a little while to really think about what she was asking me. How would I feel? Would it change the way I think about myself? She also said to me, ok maybe you have ADHD. Your brain doesn't work like everyone else's. It doesn't mean you're not exactly who you were meant to be. Your brain is yours. It's not normal or abnormal, it's yours. All you have to do is figure out how it works best for you. She even went further and said "what would you say to someone who thought they had ADHD?" That really struck me. I know exactly what I would say..... I would tell them that they are amazing and that they just think about things and situations differently. I would tell them that they have to look at it as a superpower and find a way to use that superpower the way your brain works for you. I would say that people that are different are my favorite kind of people. After that conversation she asked me if I still wanted to know if I had ADHD? My response was NO! I am exactly who I'm meant to be! #adhd #superpower #forget #story #stories #different #health #wellness #adhdwomen #adhdbrain #adhdstruggles #beauty #you #oneyou #brainfog #mom #50

If December 2022 me could meet December 2023 me, she would be shocked. She’d be broken. She be afraid. She’d be confused. I am guilty of doing all of these things this year. I fought for closure. I begged for answers. I begged for love. I wanted to know why. I wanted my future to be the way I had planned it, even if that meant a lifetime of enduring psychological abuse. I was comfortable with that. And finally, I let things be. I let people go. December 2023 me is loved every single day and I don’t have to do anything to earn love that day. I don’t have to worry about inconsistent and unpredictable moods. I don’t have to fear an outburst fueled by rage. I don’t have to walk on eggshells. I am not experiencing multiple panic attacks a week. December 2023 me is proud of myself. I broke my own heart by walking away, yes. But I also proved to myself that I am capable. That I am strong. That I can look fear in the eye and combat it. That I am deserving of a safe, steady love. Likai was a young mother who stayed in the village of Rangjyrteh, Meghalaya which is found nearby the waterfall. Widowed at a young age, Likai had to be a porter, the job of her deceased husband. She had a little baby girl who she could not give her complete attention to. Naturally, when she was home, she would spend all her time with the baby. Through the persuasion of other women from the village, who insisted that the baby needed a father, she got married to a man. The new husband turned out to be petty and was jealous of all the attention she showered on the baby when she was home. His pettiness led him to do something so ghastly, that this beautiful fall was unfortunate to be tagged with One day he cooked a hearty meal for his wife. Likai who came home after a long day of work was starving. She looked around for her baby but could not find her. Assuming that the baby was in the neighbour's house, she settled down to eat the meal cooked by her husband. I hope you see where this tragic story is going. The man was so envious of the baby, that he chopped the poor baby and cooked her for the meal that he fed to Likai! He threw away the head and bones of the baby before Likai reached home!! Unaware of this horrendous act, Likai sat down to eat her routine betel leaves and nuts after having meals. Near the basket of betel leaves, Likai saw a tiny finger that she knew belonged to her daughter. She wrapped her head around what had taken place. Petrified and enraged of the events, she ran and ran till she reached the edge of the falls, and finally jumped to her own death. Due to this incident, the waterfall is named as Nohkalikai Falls. If you're still reading, I wish you have a great day!❤️. Often the most feared part of a cruise to Antarctica is crossing the Drake Passage. It’s something you can’t predict by month or season, you just have to see what shakes out for your sailing! On our way south we had almost a Drake Lake as it’s called with 2 -3 meter swells only occasionally. It was not bad at all - we were able to carry on with our regularly scheduled days of meals and lectures with some gentle swaying here and there. On the way back however things got a little more exciting! We had 5-7 meter swells which sent some of us and our belongings flying! The crew was amazing at helping people move around the ship and informing us on how to stay safe as we passed through rough waters. I know some people suffered quite a bit during the passages, but we quite enjoyed ourselves, feeling grateful to experience both the Drake Lake and the Drake Shake to really complete our Antarctica experience. #drakeshake #antarctica #drakepassage #antarcticadventure #antarcticaexpedition @antarctica_21 @adventurelifetravel #TravelMadeYourWay #TravelGoals, #adventuretravel, #adventurecruise #antarcticaoriginal
